pros:
Great staff and supervising attorneys; 
many law school students learn to write legal appellate briefs and gain great experiences doing so; 
very flexible work hours;
the director, Peter Blanck is a very knowledgeable, friendly, and caring person and it was an honor getting to know him.

cons:
The appellate briefs were quite difficult to master at first, but one the experience in doing a few of them makes the rest of the work much easier; 
one issue is that the work can be pretty repetitive if you have done them many times over and over again;
pay was $14/hour for research assistant, at least it was from May 2018 - July 2020.
